cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper discusses data augmentation techniques in deep neural network training, which is a common topic in the fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper specifically mentions image data augmentation, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of heuristics and optimization techniques also suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the interpretation and computation of measures, which could also place it in the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
